In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 11 as Patriot Day and National Day of Service and Remembrance. He reflects on the tragic events of September 11, 2001, when thousands of innocent lives were lost in terrorist attacks. He highlights the heroism and unity that emerged in the aftermath of the attacks, and encourages Americans to honor those who were lost by serving their communities and showing compassion to those in need. The President urges Americans to visit www.Serve.gov to find ways to get involved in their communities. He also calls for the flag of the United States to be displayed at half-staff on Patriot Day and National Day of Service and Remembrance. The President invites governors, organizations, and individuals to join in the observance and calls for appropriate ceremonies, activities, and remembrance services to take place. He requests a moment of silence at 8:46 a.m. Eastern Daylight Time to honor the victims of the attacks.